# Supabase Cursor Rules

## Auth
- Use `supabase.auth.signInWithPassword()` for email/password
- Use `supabase.auth.signInWithOAuth()` for social login
- Listen to auth state: `supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange()`
- Use `getUser()` server-side (secure), `getSession()` client-side

## Database
- Use Row Level Security (RLS) on ALL tables — no exceptions
- Define RLS policies: `auth.uid() = user_id` pattern
- Use database functions for complex business logic
- Use realtime subscriptions for live data: `supabase.channel()`

## Edge Functions
- Use Deno runtime for Edge Functions
- Handle CORS in every function
- Validate inputs before processing
- Use `supabase.auth.getUser()` for authenticated functions

## Storage
- Use storage buckets with RLS policies
- Generate signed URLs for private files
- Use image transformations for thumbnails

## Best Practices
- DO: Enable RLS on every table immediately
- DO: Use Supabase client library (not raw HTTP)
- DON'T: Expose service_role key to the client
- DON'T: Skip RLS policies — even for "simple" apps
